author: @lambda-snail
text: I think it's really interesting that we humans assume that the room we are in will be the same when you return to it after five minutes. Just because that has been the experience for all rooms a person has been in, doesn't mean it will happen the next time he returns to a room, right? Perhaps the difficulties AI have with these kind of "inconsistencies" are actually telling us something deep about humans? Anyway, thank you for the video :)
